column56: When a new person joins the Ambassador program , they should be tols about the benefits apart from the regular email like how to apply for the speaker bureau, cloud accounts for meetups, one time swag stickers for meetups. Also CNCF should help in setting up the infra for video recording for  the meetups so that all meetups are live and recorded. Another point is setting up a schedule for beginner track for beginners and give that special focus meaning creating a schedule and posting it everywhere and encouraging beginners to go via that route to get the max out of the conference. Then have a fair opportunity to all  for kubernetes 101 and 201 full day trainings, have separate travel funding for CNCF ambassadors who have session at kubecon, Sendng out the notification of diversity scholorships and Travel funding little advance as VISA process take time.
More check-ins and proactively asking how help can be provided would be great! Also, more engagement to support CNCF projects in certain requests that help the community.
Regional Forums gave great chances to catch up major topics in recent KubeCon as well as local user cases. Can we share the survey result of past forums to make it better for the next ones?
